# Docs Sync Gate for Commit/PR

Before creating a git commit or pull request, perform a documentation impact check.

## Required workflow

1. Review changed files and determine whether user-facing behavior, architecture, data models, setup, or workflows changed.
2. If any of those changed, update docs in the same branch before finalizing commit/PR.
3. In your final summary, explicitly state one of:
   - "Docs updated: <paths>"
   - "No docs update required: <brief reason>"

## Docs locations to consider

- `README.md` (local dev setup only)
- `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`
- `docs/NEW_CONCEPT.md`
- `docs/NEW_LAB.md`
- `docs/MONGO.md`
- `docs/README.md` (docs index links)
- `.cursor/rules/new-concept.mdc` (when concept workflow expectations change)

## Guardrails

- Do not open a PR or conclude commit-ready work without the explicit docs status line.
- Prefer small doc updates over leaving stale docs.
